lowSESFSM%HighlightedText: [['Page 5:\n[¬s]"Participants for the SES and EAP program are all students who attended the SES or EAP program at least one session  respectively. Participants in both programs are all students who attended the SES and EAP program at least one session each. Students eligible for the SES are low-income students (deﬁned by free-and-reduced lunch status) attending a school in the second year of corrective action through NCLB. Eligibility for EAP is deﬁned as any student attending a district school providing EAP services. To be eligible to participate in both programs  the student has to be a low- income student attending a school in the second year of corrective action through and attending a school offering EAP services. Because virtually all district students are eligible for the EAP program  the students who are counted as eligible for both programs are the same students who are considered eligible for SES.[¬e]"']]
